Dialogue: 0,00:02:48.75,00:02:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Dr. Ross, we've got \Nsatellite from the Congo.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:02:53.46,00:02:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- What did he say, Rudy? \N- I can't repeat it here.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:56.22,00:02:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's Charles. \N- It's Charles.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:59.68,00:03:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- It won't work. \N- He changed the code?
Dialogue: 0,00:03:01.93,00:03:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The old man's got me changing it \Nevery three hours.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:04.43,00:03:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- Rudy, Rudy, Rudy, Rudy. \N- Very inventive.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:09.81,00:03:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just in time. \NWe should have a visual momentarily.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:12.27,00:03:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- They said they found it. \N- You're kidding.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:14.90,00:03:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven volcanoes, and he picks the right \None. His luck's finally changed.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:21.07,00:03:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- Karen. \N- I read you, Charles. And I see you.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:24.54,00:03:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Well, eureka and all that. \NI found the bloody thing.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:03:28.87,00:03:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- What was that? \N- The <i>usual.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:03:31.59,00:03:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>This whole place does the shimmy.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:03:33.67,00:03:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- How's the volcano? \N- Acting very much like</i> a <i>volcano...</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:03:36.67,00:03:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>thank you very much.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:03:38.47,00:03:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>They tell me it's fine, \Nbut I wouldn't build condominiums.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:03:41.76,00:03:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles, did you really find it?
Dialogue: 0,00:03:46.10,00:03:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Chemically flawless, \Nblue diamond alluvia.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:03:51.48,00:03:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Johnny-on-the-spot phasic laser.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:03:54.44,00:03:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>This will look kind of raw \Nwithout a real diamond.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:04:08.41,00:04:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Would you say that test \Ncame back positive?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:04:11.04,00:04:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:14.04,00:04:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>We found the sand in a mineral stream. \NJeffrey's searching for the source.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:04:18.38,00:04:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- I'll get Travis. \N- Wait. Jeffrey should share the glory.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:04:22.89,00:04:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- Let's link up again in, uh, one hour. \N- Great.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:04:26.10,00:04:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- See you <i>in</i> an <i>hour.</i> \N- Give me your coordinates.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:30.06,00:04:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Char...? Charles...?
Dialogue: 0,00:04:36.61,00:04:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jeffrey. \N- Charlie, over here.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:42.45,00:04:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Charlie, I think this \Nmay be really something.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:46.41,00:04:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- We haven't got much time. \N<i>- I'll</i> show you.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:51.12,00:04:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Jump in.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:54.84,00:04:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- What? \N<i>- I'll</i> go first.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:02.63,00:05:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I Jeffrey!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:21.07,00:05:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I Jeffrey!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:26.78,00:05:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- What is this? \N- Come on.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:30.75,00:05:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,From below it just looks like jungle, \Nbut it's not just jungle. See?
Dialogue: 0,00:05:35.33,00:05:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:38.17,00:05:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a big deal. \NThis is a big find.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:42.67,00:05:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it's just sitting here. \NAll these centuries, waiting for lucky us.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:53.73,00:05:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I raised Houston, \Nthey're getting the old man.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:58.15,00:06:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on camera and share the glory.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:00.78,00:06:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- We'll have to get another team here. \N- All right. Let me grab my bag.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:16.83,00:06:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- Perfect, you say? A flawless diamond? \N- He found it. He was right.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:21.34,00:06:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,With the right laser and diamonds...
Dialogue: 0,00:06:23.22,00:06:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we can dominate \Nthe communications industry over night.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:26.05,00:06:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Has he found the source?
Dialogue: 0,00:06:27.39,00:06:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles says a laser with a diamond \Nlike that can punch a hole in the moon.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:31.72,00:06:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh. Don't say any more out here.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:34.43,00:06:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where is he? \N- I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:36.14,00:06:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- He should have transmitted 10 minutes ago. \N- Ugh.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:39.31,00:06:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- Activate the remote. \N- Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:47.95,00:06:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- I guess he's still looking for Jeffrey. \N- Hmm. Pan the camera.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:00.75,00:07:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What in God's name...?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:09.97,00:07:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Lock your remote. Back scan. \NGive me thermal readout.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:17.73,00:07:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- I can see seven dead people. \N- What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:36.50,00:07:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- I didn't see him. Charles! \N- What?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:41.33,00:07:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- I'll</i> get help. \N- You can't get out. I had the code changed.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:44.38,00:07:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:47.13,00:07:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Rudy?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:48.55,00:07:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sir? \N- Use the fire extinguisher on that.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:57.39,00:08:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- No one knows this happened but us. \N- Families have to be be notified. Your wife.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:02.19,00:08:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know he's dead. \NIf it's reported, they'll close the border.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:06.32,00:08:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- What was that thing? \N- Uh, baboon.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:08.99,00:08:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- I thought it was a gorilla, but I've never... \N- Gorillas didn't kill. Gorillas don't do that.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:13.70,00:08:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- It could have been locals, a rival company. \N- Not another paranoid fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:17.79,00:08:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I need those diamonds, Dr. Ross!
Dialogue: 0,00:08:20.25,00:08:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Are you for real? \N- It's the future.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:22.71,00:08:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- Most believe children are the future. \N- 40,000 people, they all depend on me.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:29.26,00:08:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This satellite is our cash cow.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:31.89,00:08:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In three years it'll be obsolete. I need \Na new cash machine. This diamond's it!
Dialogue: 0,00:08:37.35,00:08:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- Charles knew it. That's why he went. \N- He went into the Congo to please you.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:42.73,00:08:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- I know you had feelings for him. \N- I almost married him.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:46.48,00:08:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to me, talking like he's...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:48.69,00:08:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to go down there, Dr. Ross.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:50.57,00:08:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're good in the field. You were \Ngood in Panama. Once you're local...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:54.03,00:08:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that laser's power pack \Nshould give off a readable signal.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:57.16,00:09:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Find some expedition that's already going. \NTake it over.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:00.50,00:09:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,00:09:02.08,00:09:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no time! Once we let out what's \Nhappened, Zaire will shut the border.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:06.13,00:09:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- By the time the investigation's... \N- Are you human?
Dialogue: 0,00:09:08.59,00:09:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be human later. Hire people \Nwhen you get there. Good people.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:12.84,00:09:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind, I'll have some waiting.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:14.89,00:09:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- Find out what happened to Charles. \N- Tell me you love your son.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:17.93,00:09:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- I do. \N- And that's why you're sending me.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:20.23,00:09:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It is.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:22.31,00:09:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. But if I have one moment when \NI think otherwise, I'll make you sorry.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:28.23,00:09:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a promise.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:38.37,00:09:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Oakland's number one classic station...</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:09:40.75,00:09:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>taking you back in time, all the time.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:09:43.12,00:09:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>There's \Na crazy little shack</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:09:45.21,00:09:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. Isn't that beautiful? \NWhat's Amy's favorite color?
Dialogue: 0,00:09:51.21,00:09:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Green, that's right. \NHow green was my valley... Drop that!
Dialogue: 0,00:09:57.35,00:10:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Pretty. So pretty.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:01.56,00:10:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Amy, on the paper. Yeah, okay, good.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:07.02,00:10:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, get some more paint.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:11.07,00:10:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. That's green.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:14.03,00:10:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Amy, on the paper. \NOn... On the paper.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:19.58,00:10:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy! Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,00:10:26.50,00:10:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- How did she sleep? \N- Great night.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:28.38,00:10:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- No nightmares? \N- Not a one.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:30.34,00:10:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Good girl.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:32.13,00:10:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my Amy.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:35.01,00:10:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Richard, you better clean her up. \NIt's showtime.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:40.64,00:10:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When we started out, it was so simple.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:43.06,00:10:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Communication is what separated \Nhuman from animal. Speech.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:48.23,00:10:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And for those humans who had \Nam impairment that inhibited speech...
Dialogue: 0,00:10:51.86,00:10:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,sign language. An alphabet in gestures.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:54.69,00:10:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Words in motion. Then came virtual reality.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:58.24,00:11:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensors worn like clothing could read \Nand replicate the body's movements.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:04.37,00:11:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Arliss Wender at MIT was the first to \Napply this technology to sign language.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:11.00,00:11:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Our subject, William, \Nwas born without the organs of speech.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:11:16.05,00:11:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Isn't that right, William?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:11:19.22,00:11:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>That is absolutely right.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:11:28.56,00:11:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>This is the first time \NI have ever heard my own voice.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:11:38.20,00:11:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Lights, please. \NIt's hard to get grants for what I do.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:43.08,00:11:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people just don't believe it. \NThey think it's a parlor trick. A gag.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:49.54,00:11:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's no gag, ladies and gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:51.84,00:11:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,With this new technology, \NI can demonstrate it...
Dialogue: 0,00:11:54.50,00:11:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way it has never been possible \Nto demonstrate it before.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:59.13,00:12:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Animals can talk.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:02.05,00:12:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, could you come down \Nhere please?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:19.32,00:12:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Amy. Thank you for the flowers.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:22.99,00:12:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Peter. Hello, Peter.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:12:25.54,00:12:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:28.25,00:12:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, how old are you?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:32.17,00:12:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Amy 7. Amy good gorilla.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:12:38.21,00:12:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- Amy pretty. \N</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:12:41.22,00:12:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, look at me.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:43.60,00:12:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- Amy mother. \N- That's right. That's your baby.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:49.14,00:12:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- Amy wants lunch.</i> \N- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:54.11,00:12:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- What do you think, Mrs. Romy? \N- It's spooky. Very spooky.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:59.19,00:13:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy's above average intelligence \Nfor a gorilla, but she's not a freak.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:04.78,00:13:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What she has learned, \Nother gorillas have learned and can learn.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:08.70,00:13:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But that takes money, of course. \NIsn't that right, Amy?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:30.77,00:13:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, calm down. Easy.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:33.06,00:13:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hey! Shh, shh. \NIt's okay. You're all right.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:38.32,00:13:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- You've got her sedated. She'll be fine. \N- She's not gonna be fine. Nightmares again.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:44.41,00:13:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's happened before. Gorillas in captivity \Ndegenerating mentally, having to be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:49.66,00:13:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When she did these paintings \Nshe got better. Why?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:56.13,00:14:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey... \NWhat's this room starting to look like?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:04.01,00:14:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- The Jungle, she's been painting the jungle! \N- I don't know, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:07.22,00:14:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She wants to go home.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:08.51,00:14:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter, you did a great job. You taught a \Ngorilla to talk, to paint, for gosh sakes.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:14.52,00:14:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When it comes to Amy, you can get a grant \Nfor anything except setting her free.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:18.57,00:14:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How about this. I taught her, \Nnow she can teach them.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:21.40,00:14:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- Who? \N- The mountain gorillas.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:23.15,00:14:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We can translate \Nwhat other animals are saying.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:26.41,00:14:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, please. Making you Dr. Doolittle?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:29.70,00:14:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't a foundation in motion that would \Nfund an expedition with that objective.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:34.66,00:14:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I will pay.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:37.17,00:14:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- I will pay for Amy to go home. \N- And who are you?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:42.17,00:14:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Herkermer Homolka. Formerly of Romania. \NFree now of the chains of Ceaucescu.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:47.47,00:14:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Traveling the world, doing good.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:53.89,00:14:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- A Romanian philanthropist? \N- Herkermer Homolka.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:56.39,00:14:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- Something's voodoo. \N- Don't look a gift horse in the mouth.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:59.36,00:15:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's penetrating. \NWe're taking Amy home. Get packed.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:04.36,00:15:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know where we're going? \NAmy, where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:08.91,00:15:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jungle. <i>Me</i> jungle. \N- She's really excited.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:12.70,00:15:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- Are you excited? \N- Me? I'm terrified.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:16.62,00:15:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jungle. \N- Safari? I don't even like picnics. Nice glasses.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:20.59,00:15:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>\NJungle. Me jungle.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:15:22.88,00:15:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- That's right. Jungle. Home. \N- Tickle me. Tickle me.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:15:28.64,00:15:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, time to go.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:40.77,00:15:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone looking for me?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:44.15,00:15:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Herkermer Homolka, hello. \NUh, the transport.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:48.61,00:15:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. Um...
Dialogue: 0,00:15:50.20,00:15:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- ls there a problem? \N- Not unless there's a problem.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:59.62,00:16:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you excited, sweetheart? That's a \Ncamera. Be careful, it's expensive.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:04.05,00:16:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I think she's got a real eye.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:07.22,00:16:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- Karen Ross. Professor Karen Ross. \N- Professor Peter Elliot.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:12.10,00:16:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- Doctor. \N- Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:13.64,00:16:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you got my faxes, \NFed Exes and phone calls?
Dialogue: 0,00:16:16.43,00:16:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm sorry, you're the one. \N- Yes, I'm the one.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:18.69,00:16:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We've put together a hasty expedition.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:20.90,00:16:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,To the Congo, with a talking gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:23.23,00:16:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jungle me. Jungle. <i>Tickle</i> Amy. \N- That's right, jungle. Just a minute, Amy.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:27.28,00:16:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm sorry... I'm afraid that's impossible. \N- I need to join up with you.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:31.16,00:16:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- Excuse me. \N- Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,00:16:32.78,00:16:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- I have all the visas. \N- Go ahead and load this stuff on the plane.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:36.12,00:16:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- We're taking this stuff off the plane. \N- Off the plane?
Dialogue: 0,00:16:38.79,00:16:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- I can pay part of the cost. \N- Why take stuff off the plane?
Dialogue: 0,00:16:42.46,00:16:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm sorry, we don't need any money. \N- You're flying way under capacity.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:46.75,00:16:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can easily find room for me.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:48.46,00:16:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's not a matter of that. It's Amy. \N<i>- Ugly</i> woman.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:52.34,00:16:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- The gorilla? \N- She gets jealous very easily.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:54.72,00:16:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody tell me \Nwhy you're unloading the plane.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:57.22,00:16:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- Talk to the operations guy. \N- Can't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,00:16:59.89,00:17:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- No. \N- I've gotta get on this plane.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:02.06,00:17:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to be listed with your manifest, \Nor my visas are worthless. Name your price.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:06.27,00:17:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a price. I'm not a pound \Nof sugar, I'm a primatologist.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:09.57,00:17:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be hasty, Dr. Elliot.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:12.91,00:17:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Herkermer Homolka, \Nformerly of Romania.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:15.83,00:17:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- Dr. Karen Ross. \N- There seems to be some glitch.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:18.79,00:17:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- They're unloading the plane. \N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:22.87,00:17:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately there has been \Na slight interruption in my credit flow.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:27.46,00:17:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- I am unable to pay for the fuel. \N- I'll pay for the fuel.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:31.26,00:17:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- I'll</i> pay for it. How much is the fuel? \N- Fifty-six thousand dollars.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:35.80,00:17:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifty-six thousand?
Dialogue: 0,00:17:38.77,00:17:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you smiling about?
Dialogue: 0,00:17:40.52,00:17:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You need me, Dr. Elliot.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:49.19,00:17:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Taxi to</i> \Nrunway, three-one <i>left.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:17:52.78,00:17:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>This is your captain speaking.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:17:54.61,00:17:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- Hey. \N- We've been cleared for take-off.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:17:56.82,00:18:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Please make sure that your seat belts \Nare fastened and that all carry-on...</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:18:00.87,00:18:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We're returning her to the jungle \Nfrom whence she came.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:04.62,00:18:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,From the look of it, not a moment too soon.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:07.54,00:18:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it. Good girl. Here's an egg.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:12.97,00:18:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Unh.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:14.13,00:18:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We do not throw things. \N- ls that animal dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,00:18:17.85,00:18:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans are dangerous, \Ngorillas are very gentle.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:25.85,00:18:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay, Amy.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:27.23,00:18:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Where ground?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:18:29.82,00:18:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where ground? \N- It's fine. We're flying.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:32.15,00:18:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- We're going to the jungle. \N- Amy want <i>green</i> drop <i>drink.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:18:37.45,00:18:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- No. \N- Amy want green drop drink.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:18:42.08,00:18:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, all right.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:45.04,00:18:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd swear they were married.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:47.75,00:18:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The notion of the "killer ape" may be politically \Nincorrect, but that's not to say it's untrue.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:53.88,00:18:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe what I'm hearing.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:57.34,00:19:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Cliches usually contain some \Nelement of truth.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:06.14,00:19:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- Are you serving that ape a martini? \N- She's allowed one. It'll calm her down.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:13.07,00:19:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In my life I have heard \Nmany a bizarre story.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:16.99,00:19:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Many a bizarre story \Ncontaining bizarre truth.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:47.69,00:19:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- There you go. Watch your step. \N- Dr. Ross!
Dialogue: 0,00:19:53.32,00:19:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- Dr. Ross! \N- Hello?
Dialogue: 0,00:19:56.53,00:20:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Eddie Ventro. Mr Travis asked me \Nto meet your plane, set up your expedition.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:02.37,00:20:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Her expedition? She's just along for the ride. \N- Whatever. Be an asshole.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:06.70,00:20:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- Who is this guy? \N- Eddie Ventro, transportation and equipment.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:11.50,00:20:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't supply assholes with new \Npersonalities. Wanna see your new plane?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:16.13,00:20:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go! Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:21.76,00:20:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- Wanna sell that gorilla? \N- No.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:23.93,00:20:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- Worth a lot of money. \N- How much?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:25.64,00:20:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- Mr. Homolka, I can't believe you. \N- I'm just curious.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:28.27,00:20:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty, twenty-five grand for a female.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:31.31,00:20:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- Amy want to go home. Go home. \N- I'm taking you home,</i> Amy.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:36.36,00:20:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, a talking gorilla! I feel the money hairs \Non the back of my neck going woo, woo, woo.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:42.62,00:20:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Travis told me to load you up. The \Nworks. You know how to use all this stuff?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:47.08,00:20:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll get by. \N- You really need a balloon?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:49.46,00:20:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't. Let me see that.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:52.83,00:20:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- Who are they? \N- Hi, fellas!
Dialogue: 0,00:20:55.84,00:20:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuck if I know. Don't ask. \NWe're on our third government in two years.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:59.76,00:21:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- So are you our guide? \N- No, I stay at the airport.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:02.72,00:21:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Supposing you got Monroe Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:04.35,00:21:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- Is he good? \N- He's very good. He's also very late.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:08.10,00:21:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:09.56,00:21:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- Holy shit, now what? \N- What was that?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:11.98,00:21:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't got a clue. I feel like \Nthis airport's just gone to shit.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:24.37,00:21:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- All right, give me your passports. \N- We already arranged for a guide.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:28.95,00:21:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Robertson Reynolds. \N- Yeah, I fired him.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:30.08,00:21:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- You what? \N- Reynolds is a bird-watcher.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:32.96,00:21:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- I hired Robertson Reynolds. \N- You would.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:35.46,00:21:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You have any idea what's going on \Nin the Congo as of this morning?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:39.13,00:21:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kigani have had it with Zaire \Nand they're eating people.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:42.84,00:21:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You go in with Reynolds, you're coming out \Nsomebody's bowel movement.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:46.43,00:21:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go. Now wasn't that \Neasier than going through customs?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:49.81,00:21:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Monroe.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:52.77,00:21:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- Guess what? \N- What?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:54.90,00:21:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- We need to switch airports. \N- Oh, shit, why?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:57.36,00:21:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Bomb in the president's car.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:58.98,00:22:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the president's car? \NDid they get him?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:01.49,00:22:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the bad news. No, they didn't.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:04.36,00:22:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- I hope you folks have lots of money. \N- We do.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:15.96,00:22:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Now run away. \NOh, come on, man, run away.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:20.34,00:22:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- Get in the back. \N- What about equipment?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:22.63,00:22:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave it to Eddie. I would hurry, really.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:24.88,00:22:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Is this normal? \N- Get in the truck.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:26.72,00:22:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're on your own, Eddie. \N- Yeah, how I like it.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:31.56,00:22:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where do you want me to set you up? \N- Get a DC-3.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:34.44,00:22:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A grass strip south of Kegoma. Get it \Nstripped. Keep this from the company.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:38.19,00:22:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,First the Kigani in Zaire, now this godfather \Nstuff. Not a good day to be in Africa.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:43.07,00:22:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- Lower the flaps. \N- So long, good luck!
Dialogue: 0,00:22:45.61,00:22:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now sit down.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:08.55,00:23:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting out of here. Unh!
Dialogue: 0,00:23:20.48,00:23:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's going on? \N- Are we safe?
Dialogue: 0,00:23:25.36,00:23:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right, just bumpy. \NJust a few bumps.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:33.12,00:23:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, leave that man alone.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:41.09,00:23:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, don't inhale.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:45.17,00:23:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- Karen Ross? \N- That's me.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:48.26,00:23:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Monroe Kelly. \NI'm your great white hunter for this trip.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:51.39,00:23:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- Though I happen to be black. \N- How bad is this news for us?
Dialogue: 0,00:23:56.39,00:24:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever the leadership of one of these little \NCentral African countries comes into question...
Dialogue: 0,00:24:01.27,00:24:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,they tend to murder everybody.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:03.11,00:24:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, my God! \N- Not really?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:05.28,00:24:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They live for the opportunity \Nto settle scores.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:07.74,00:24:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And they've got a lot of scores to settle. \NIt's like what's going on in the Congo.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:12.41,00:24:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- Things are pretty bad in the Congo. \N- We heard.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:15.87,00:24:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kigani are pissed off.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:18.75,00:24:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't blame them. The 20th century sucks. \NMaybe the 21st will be better.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:24.17,00:24:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- You some kind of criminal, aren't you? \N- Aren't we all?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:27.13,00:24:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'm not a criminal, I'm a scientist.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:29.88,00:24:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Scientist?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:31.76,00:24:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I run a few guns, \Nyou sons of bitches ruin the world.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:36.52,00:24:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's a good idea to have \Nfurther involvement with these people.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:40.56,00:24:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you suggest we do, Dr. Elliot?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:43.40,00:24:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as we can, \Nwe should go our own way.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:47.48,00:24:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ugh. \N- Don't I know you?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:51.74,00:24:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps. I travel a great deal.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:55.45,00:24:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are you doing with that gorilla? \N- Taking her home.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:58.45,00:25:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She was caught \Nin the Virunga region of the Congo.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:01.12,00:25:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to try and take her back \Nto the farm now that she's seen Paris?
Dialogue: 0,00:25:05.71,00:25:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- And this is your cover? \N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:10.63,00:25:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty good. Or, it would have been.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:13.09,00:25:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm nobody's cover. Cover for what? \N- You find yourself in the middle of something.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:17.51,00:25:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Cover for what? \N- I don't know, and she won't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:20.56,00:25:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But the kind of money \Nher company is throwing around?
Dialogue: 0,00:25:23.31,00:25:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't spend that for any gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:27.61,00:25:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Relax. You're in better hands \Nthan you should be.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:14.11,00:26:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- Monroe. \N- Captain Wanta.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:17.95,00:26:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you? \NMiss Ross, such a pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:25.83,00:26:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Have some, uh, coffee and cake.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:33.34,00:26:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You have our visas. Our manifest. \NThis is a legitimate scientific mission.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:37.43,00:26:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no right to detain us.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:39.51,00:26:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Liar, liar, pants on fire.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:43.81,00:26:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So says my computer, Miss Ross.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:50.90,00:26:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. You used to work for the CIA. \NAnd now you're TraviCom.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:55.53,00:26:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- TraviCom pays better than the CIA? \N- You have a big mouth.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:59.53,00:27:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody says that about me. \NWhat can I do?
Dialogue: 0,00:27:04.62,00:27:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Monroe, you have \Nthe worst timing in the world.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:07.29,00:27:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me about it.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:08.58,00:27:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They blew up the president's Mercedes, \Ndid you know?
Dialogue: 0,00:27:11.25,00:27:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a big plot. Our country will \Nbe in shit for at least a year.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:15.80,00:27:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Captain, I need that truck. \N- You need the truck.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:18.22,00:27:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You also need ten good men to the border.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:30.11,00:27:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,More.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:45.79,00:27:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Homolka?
Dialogue: 0,00:27:49.83,00:27:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:51.63,00:27:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop eating my sesame cake.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:54.88,00:27:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:57.97,00:28:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing in my country, \Nyou bag of shit?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:01.76,00:28:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, please. \NI only wish to explore and discover.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:06.48,00:28:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This fellow is a big bag of shit.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:12.77,00:28:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Shake this rat from off your neck. He owes \Nmoney to everybody everywhere he goes.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:18.82,00:28:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I will ask you to wait outside, Mr. \NHomolka.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:26.58,00:28:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's the gorilla that's going \Nto get you across the border safely.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:31.21,00:28:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's so afraid of being seen in an \NAmerican movie being cruel to a gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:37.05,00:28:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the crazy world we live in. \NOkay, you can go.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:43.80,00:28:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit the road, as they say. \NAnd have a nice day.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:04.95,00:29:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- You all right? \N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:06.87,00:29:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Admit it, you're glad to see me.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:57.96,00:30:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- Kahega! \N- Ah, Monroe!
Dialogue: 0,00:30:03.34,00:30:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Kikuyu tribesman, very nice guy.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:05.47,00:30:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- Are we in Zaire? \N- Tanzania.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:26.62,00:30:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay close to me. Amy. Amy, come on.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:41.38,00:30:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- Somehow, I think this is at my expense. \N- You're right.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:50.10,00:30:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When do you think we will \Nget to the rainforest?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:53.06,00:30:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- Herkermer Homolka, right? \N- Yes. Hi, hello.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:56.27,00:30:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not looking for \NSolomon's city again, are you?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:59.19,00:31:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,00:31:01.32,00:31:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Homolka was part of \Na disastrous expedition...
Dialogue: 0,00:31:04.03,00:31:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- about, what, five years ago? \N- I would prefer you...
Dialogue: 0,00:31:06.82,00:31:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They were looking for a city called Zinj. \NUnfortunately, it doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:10.70,00:31:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- It does exist! \N- Fine.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:12.91,00:31:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Three members of his safari \Ndied from exposure.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:15.91,00:31:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- A fourth was shot by we don't know who. \N- It was an appalling suicide.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:20.42,00:31:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't quibble. And Mr. Homolka \Nhad to be carried out of the jungle...
Dialogue: 0,00:31:24.38,00:31:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,by, as I remember it, me.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:26.13,00:31:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew he wasn't a Romanian philanthropist.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:28.59,00:31:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he's Romanian. And he has \Ndone good, but mostly for Mr. Homolka.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:40.31,00:31:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's all this stuff? \N- Courtesy of Eddie Ventro.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:43.61,00:31:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Eddie! What happened?
Dialogue: 0,00:31:45.11,00:31:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh. A customs guy hit me with a can \Nof peanut oil for stamping visas.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:50.20,00:31:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm never going back to that country, man.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:52.33,00:31:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- Those people have permanently wigged out. \N- Ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:54.62,00:31:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- Dr. Ross. \N- Hi.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:56.29,00:32:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Equipment list. You got everything but the \Nballoon and the home entertainment center.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:01.54,00:32:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ah. Your boss says "Call me." \N- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:04.67,00:32:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You got 11 good guys, significant \Nfirepower, significant technology.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:08.76,00:32:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,More than that \NI don't think you're gonna need. Agree?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:11.43,00:32:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- I agree. \N- Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:12.89,00:32:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- Bye, Eddie. \N- Bye, Monroe.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:39.33,00:32:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- May I? \N- There's one thing I don't understand, Monroe.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:43.29,00:32:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that, Dr. Elliot?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:44.67,00:32:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If the border to Zaire is shut...
Dialogue: 0,00:32:46.55,00:32:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- how do we get across? \N- Luck.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:11.82,00:33:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,00:33:13.70,00:33:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell is that?
Dialogue: 0,00:33:16.87,00:33:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit. I thought we'd get farther. \NI'd put her out now.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:22.12,00:33:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, you would? Who's firing on us? \N- Kahega!
Dialogue: 0,00:33:24.96,00:33:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We crossed the border into Zaire. \NWe're violating airspace.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:27.92,00:33:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- She likes bananas? \N- Sure.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:29.59,00:33:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, eat this, darling. \NShe's going to feel great.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:32.93,00:33:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- What do you mean? \N- Something to keep her calm. Gorilla Prozac.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:38.85,00:33:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- Can we make it to Bondo? \N- I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,00:33:40.85,00:33:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That last one was a heat-seeker. \NWe're done.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:56.45,00:33:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are you doing? \N- Step aside, please.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:21.06,00:34:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Hey-</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:34:46.29,00:34:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Ross. Here.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:51.00,00:34:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why are they putting on parachutes? \N- Figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:54.05,00:34:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Take it. \N- Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,00:35:09.19,00:35:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- This isn't gonna work. \N- Yes it is. I'll take Amy.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:13.78,00:35:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- She might get hurt. I can't risk it. \N- You know how to fly this plane?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:17.16,00:35:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- No. \N- The pilot and co-pilot are gone.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:19.41,00:35:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:22.91,00:35:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:25.21,00:35:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Go! Go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,00:35:38.30,00:35:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Push me, please.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:42.10,00:35:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Harder, please.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:05.37,00:36:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You want me to push you too?
Dialogue: 0,00:36:11.79,00:36:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,See you down there.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:16.30,00:36:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,00:37:22.28,00:37:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where's Amy? \N- Now she's asleep.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:24.95,00:37:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there. On the way down, \Nshe decided to wake up.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:28.24,00:37:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- And that little lady has some set of teeth. \N- I'm sorry, but we have to call this off.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:33.12,00:37:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- I beg your pardon? \N- I'm in over my head.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:35.13,00:37:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm not James Bond. \N- Don't worry, I'll take care of you.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:37.96,00:37:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want you to take care of me.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:40.97,00:37:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. I'm taking a safari \Ninto the Virunga region of the Congo.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:45.18,00:37:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to go, just go wherever.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:48.60,00:37:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But you should know this is a dangerous \Nplace, and people die here very easily.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:54.10,00:37:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:04.53,00:38:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:10.70,00:38:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy? Amy!
Dialogue: 0,00:38:14.04,00:38:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:23.26,00:38:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Such an extraordinary animal.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:26.97,00:38:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Those paintings. Do you think she was \Ndrawing something she saw in life?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:31.89,00:38:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Or in a dream, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:33.39,00:38:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- I think she was drawing a jungle, home. \N- What about those oval shapes?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:37.77,00:38:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- Just a shape she likes, something like that. \N- Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:42.61,00:38:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- Video game? \N- It gives latitude and longitude.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:45.74,00:38:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- More than that, from the look of it. \N- Well, you know, it's a gadget. It has features.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:50.95,00:38:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're picking up a signal. \NSomeone or something?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:53.83,00:38:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- A little bit Of both. \N- Ah.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:55.92,00:39:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- So why did you quit the CIA? \N- I never worked for the CIA.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:00.25,00:39:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you didn't.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:01.59,00:39:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you had worked for the CIA, \Nwhy would you quit?
Dialogue: 0,00:39:04.63,00:39:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're a loveless bunch \Nof sons of bitches.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:07.18,00:39:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- And you're not? \N- And I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:10.14,00:39:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:18.90,00:39:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- Okay, here we go. \N- Ah. Fabulous equipment.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:23.69,00:39:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- Best of the best. \N- I have air-conditioning, too.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:26.28,00:39:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Air-conditioners?
Dialogue: 0,00:39:28.41,00:39:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- I suppose it is a bit much. \N- Shit, I'll take one.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:36.37,00:39:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:42.75,00:39:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Homolka...
Dialogue: 0,00:39:44.96,00:39:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- Please, call me Herkermer. \N- All right. You can call me Mr. Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:52.68,00:39:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- I wonder what she's about. \N- What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,00:39:57.14,00:39:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,She's after something. \NYou're after something.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:59.60,00:40:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're after, I've got figured. \NBut what she's after, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:03.61,00:40:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get you! I'll get you!
Dialogue: 0,00:40:06.07,00:40:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm helping that young scientist \Nreturn his ward to the wild.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:11.70,00:40:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He says the ape may be able to tell us \Nthe thoughts of the wild gorillas.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:16.12,00:40:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well I can tell you your thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:17.08,00:40:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're looking for King Solomon's \Ndiamonds. The lost city of Zinj.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:24.46,00:40:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- I've given it up. \N- You'll never give it up.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:26.92,00:40:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is, Herkermer, \Nit doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:29.93,00:40:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Solomon must have gotten his diamonds \Nfrom Cartiers, like everybody else.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:39.56,00:40:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha-ha-ha. You like that, don't you? \NHa-ha-ha.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:45.65,00:40:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Time for Madam Amy's vitamins.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:55.08,00:40:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Karen Ross. 81452.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:58.29,00:41:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That is KR81452. \NHouston, Travis, do you read?
Dialogue: 0,00:41:04.34,00:41:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Karen Ross, 81452. \NHouston, Travis, do you read?</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:41:09.22,00:41:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I read and see you, Dr. Ross. \NCongratulations on crossing the border.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:15.47,00:41:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>I'm picking up a signal \Nfrom the laser's power pack.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:41:18.18,00:41:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Excellent. Wherever the laser is, \NCharles should be too.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:21.10,00:41:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hope so. Tomorrow we enter the \Nrainforest at the base of the volcanic range.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:25.69,00:41:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Good. Karen, I've had those images \Nof that creature analyzed. Rudy.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:41:37.24,00:41:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>What's W? \N- My primatologist tells me it's something new.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:41:40.50,00:41:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>He doesn't know what, \Nbut it's gorilla-like.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:41:42.87,00:41:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sufficiently armed?
Dialogue: 0,00:41:44.92,00:41:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Do you have enough manpower? \N<i>- Yes.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:41:47.88,00:41:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. The bad news is Geo-thermal. \NYou've got to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:51.76,00:41:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That region in the Virungas is bad. \NSometimes the volcanic activity...
Dialogue: 0,00:41:55.80,00:41:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>is breaking out of the graph. \NThe region's going to blow.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:41:58.93,00:42:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Could be a week, could be sooner. \NDr. Ross...</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:42:01.68,00:42:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- What the hell...? \N- Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,00:42:04.06,00:42:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No, dammit! Not again!
Dialogue: 0,00:42:07.86,00:42:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:13.74,00:42:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:17.20,00:42:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's completely destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:28.10,00:43:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Amy's medical supplies. \NThey can't get wet.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:55.67,00:43:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful boats. \NMoney's a wonderful thing.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:59.68,00:44:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Give her the banana with the dope inside?
Dialogue: 0,00:44:01.76,00:44:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he gave her the banana \Nwith the dope inside.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:05.39,00:44:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. Shitty Peter. I know.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:08.77,00:44:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's this?
Dialogue: 0,00:44:12.86,00:44:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:14.98,00:44:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All <i>the</i> leaves are brown
Dialogue: 0,00:44:17.53,00:44:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>And the sky is gray</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:44:20.45,00:44:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>I've been for a walk</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:44:23.08,00:44:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>On</i> a <i>winters day</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:44:25.16,00:44:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>On a winters day</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:44:27.08,00:44:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>I'd be safe and warm</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:44:30.79,00:44:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>If I was in L.A.</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:44:34.84,00:44:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- California dreaming \N- California dreaming</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:44:38.72,00:44:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>On such a winters day</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:44:42.64,00:44:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Stopped into a church</i>
Dialogue: 0,00:44:57.61,00:44:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out for the rock!
Dialogue: 0,00:45:01.11,00:45:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,00:45:03.78,00:45:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,00:45:24.01,00:45:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- What is this Zinj, Mr. Homolka? \N- I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:29.39,00:45:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been believed that King Solomon \Nhad a diamond mine in the Congo...
Dialogue: 0,00:45:32.94,00:45:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in a city called Zinj.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:34.81,00:45:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Diamonds?
Dialogue: 0,00:45:39.61,00:45:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose there's no point \Nin playing stupid.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:43.74,00:45:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall arrive there together, \Nwe shall all be rich.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:48.83,00:45:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fine with me. \NExcept there's no Zinj.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:51.75,00:45:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Half the safaris that have gone in looking \Nnever made it back.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:55.13,00:45:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The other half came back with nothing.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:57.09,00:46:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but we have a trumping card \Nthat they did not have.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:01.92,00:46:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- We do? \N- We do. That gorilla...
Dialogue: 0,00:46:06.22,00:46:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- knows where it is. \N- What?
Dialogue: 0,00:46:08.47,00:46:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The gorilla?
Dialogue: 0,00:46:10.31,00:46:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As a young man, \NI found a book in Soviet Georgia.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:14.77,00:46:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It contained a detailed drawing \Nof the city of Zinj.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:19.78,00:46:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The drawing contained \Na peculiar decoration.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:23.86,00:46:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,An open eye.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:26.41,00:46:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, on safari, I found this.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:34.33,00:46:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same symbol. Now...
Dialogue: 0,00:46:38.59,00:46:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,look at this.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:42.80,00:46:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The gorilla drew this.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:47.43,00:46:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the same image. It is the open eye.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:53.02,00:46:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That gorilla has seen the city of Zinj.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:59.82,00:47:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Have your laughing, and I will have mine.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:10.54,00:47:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit...
Dialogue: 0,00:47:13.45,00:47:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- What is it? \N- The signal stopped.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:16.79,00:47:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- Does that mean...? \N- It just means the signal stopped.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:22.51,00:47:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it means.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:24.40,00:48:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:52.97,00:48:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,00:49:04.57,00:49:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- Shoot it! \N- Amy!
Dialogue: 0,00:49:06.86,00:49:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- What is it? \N- Turn the boat around, quickly.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:13.70,00:49:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh! Aah!
Dialogue: 0,00:49:16.70,00:49:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoot it! Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,00:49:20.100,00:49:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn the boat around!
Dialogue: 0,00:49:27.09,00:49:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Head for shore!
Dialogue: 0,00:49:45.48,00:49:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- How is he? \N- It's just a big cut.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:47.48,00:49:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll stitch it up, he'll be all right. \N- Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:51.24,00:49:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's that? \N- A plane.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:54.99,00:49:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- Good luck to them. \N- Who are they?
Dialogue: 0,00:49:57.54,00:50:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, but the Zaire Air Force \Nhas got a piece of their ass.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:06.09,00:50:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Pitch camp. Tomorrow, Mt. Mukenko.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:28.98,00:50:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- She's getting excited. \N- Why, do you think?
Dialogue: 0,00:50:31.65,00:50:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere on the other side of this \Nmountain is where Amy was born.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:03.35,00:51:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, it's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:07.35,00:51:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this your valley, Amy? \NIt is, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:10.52,00:51:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's home. That's your home.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:15.78,00:51:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty jungle, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:25.54,00:51:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What's she doing?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:27.21,00:51:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She wants to go to the place in her heart.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:30.96,00:51:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- You mean the place in your heart, Herkermer. \N- You may call me Mr. Homolka.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:38.22,00:51:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Amy, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:42.64,00:51:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- We've lost two porters. \N- Where'd they go?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:44.68,00:51:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ran away. \N- And they didn't invite me?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:48.27,00:51:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You want your glove? All right, sit still.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:55.44,00:52:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This, as they say, is a fork in the road. \NWe could go left or we could go right.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:02.12,00:52:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We go the wrong way, \Nwe lose two or three days.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:04.45,00:52:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We must follow the gorilla. \NWhere she leads.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:08.96,00:52:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- That would be left. \N- Best guess...
Dialogue: 0,00:52:10.71,00:52:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,off my last coordinates was this way.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:12.88,00:52:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- That would be right. \N- Amy, Peter, <i>go</i> this way.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:19.01,00:52:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't have her passion. \NI'll follow the gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:31.81,00:52:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This doesn't seem \Nlike the right way to me.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:01.84,00:53:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Good Lord.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:07.22,00:53:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's that plane we saw burning in \Nthe sky. - Who were they?
Dialogue: 0,00:53:11.15,00:53:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Travis, my boss, thought I wasn't gonna \Nmake it. He sent another expedition.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:14.90,00:53:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Tried to push too far. Looks like a rocket \Ngot them. There's no point going in there.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:20.82,00:53:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- My God, what a waste of life. \N- We'd better keep moving.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:24.89,00:54:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, shit! Somebody help me. \N- What is it?
Dialogue: 0,00:54:28.64,00:54:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something on my... \NLike, a creature, growth or something.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:31.81,00:54:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- Look. \N- Ah. That's a leech.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:34.98,00:54:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- Take it off. \N- It's your leech, you take it off.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:38.32,00:54:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- Need some help? \N- No.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:39.90,00:54:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- Here, burn it off with this. \N- Ha-ha-ha.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:42.32,00:54:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ha, ha. \N- Ugh.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:42.99,00:54:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- Mm! \N- This is disgusting.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:52.66,00:54:53.100,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:02.55,00:55:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- Monroe? \N- Don't indicate you see them.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:07.18,00:55:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizumu. The ghost tribe. \NThere are probably 20 of them.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:14.35,00:55:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- I only see two. \N- Yes, that's how they are.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:17.60,00:55:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- Are they friendly? \N- They're sensitive. They're forest people.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:31.54,00:55:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why are they laughing? \N- They asked who was in charge, I said I was.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:35.58,00:55:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's so funny about that? \N- I'm black.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:37.88,00:55:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have luggage on my head.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:48.51,00:55:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He says there's a dead white man...
Dialogue: 0,00:55:50.64,00:55:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in this forest with a \Nsymbol on his clothes.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:58.81,00:56:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He's dead? Did they say he's dead?
Dialogue: 0,00:56:01.77,00:56:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- What does "TC" mean? \N- TraviCom. The company I work for.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:06.78,00:56:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They have several levels of "dead."
Dialogue: 0,00:56:09.11,00:56:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone's not dead \Nuntil they're completely dead.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:51.99,00:56:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven't moved him. \NThey believe his soul has left his body.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:55.54,00:56:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If they move him, his soul will be lost, \Nnever finding his body again.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:59.12,00:57:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They're calling to his soul, \Nasking it to come back.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:29.32,00:57:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is the man?
Dialogue: 0,00:57:44.88,00:57:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's not him. \N- Not who?
Dialogue: 0,00:57:46.34,00:57:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Bob Driscoll. What happened to him?
Dialogue: 0,00:57:48.92,00:57:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Bob? Bob?
Dialogue: 0,00:57:51.43,00:57:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Let's sit him up. \N- Who is this man?
Dialogue: 0,00:57:53.59,00:57:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My company sent an expedition to \Nthe Virungas. This man was with them.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:58.93,00:58:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Lay him over there.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:00.35,00:58:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- What happened to him? \N- I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:04.65,00:58:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Bob?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:36.55,00:58:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- He's dead. \N- God, no.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:47.90,00:58:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That region of the Congo is uninhabited.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:50.15,00:58:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- Something inhabits it. \N- What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:52.49,00:58:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Camp destroyed. People dead. \NA gray gorilla or something.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:55.36,00:58:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- No such thing as a gray gorilla. \N- I saw one.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:57.57,00:59:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's hard to believe. \N- Two men are unaccounted for.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:00.24,00:59:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeffrey Weems \Nand Charles Travis, my fianc.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:02.91,00:59:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- My former fianc. \N- Former?
Dialogue: 0,00:59:04.58,00:59:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd better get to him, then.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:21.93,00:59:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- What the hell is that? \N- Perimeter alarm.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:24.10,00:59:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They had it around their camp.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:26.81,00:59:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But where's the camp, their equipment?
Dialogue: 0,00:59:47.17,00:59:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand it. There had to be \N300 pounds of equipment.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:52.09,00:59:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And the bodies. \NThere's no sign of the bodies.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:22.87,01:00:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's a dead end? \N- Maybe, maybe not.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:36.38,01:00:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,01:01:30.23,01:01:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- Son of a bitch. \N- Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:33.73,01:01:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,01:01:37.32,01:01:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the city of Zinj...
Dialogue: 0,01:01:42.49,01:01:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have looked for all my life.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:51.96,01:01:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the eyes.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:56.25,01:01:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the same.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:01.13,01:02:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Kahega, guns up. Stay alert.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:09.60,01:02:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here, Amy. Stay with me.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:03.34,01:04:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,First they found the diamonds, \NSolomon's men.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:10.26,01:04:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A diamond mine of incredible bounty.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:14.93,01:04:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they built the city around \Nthe mine, so that it should be protected.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:21.73,01:04:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The savagery of the guards was legend.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:24.82,01:04:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They instantly fell upon \Nany thief, any transgressor.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:29.28,01:04:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The diamonds flowed \Nto the kingdom of Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:33.58,01:04:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened? Why did the city die?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:35.87,01:04:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't know. \N- Maybe the mines ran dry.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:38.29,01:04:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No! No, the diamonds are here!
Dialogue: 0,01:04:41.63,01:04:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Monroe, over here! \N- What is it?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:48.68,01:04:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,On the step, by the hood.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:50.76,01:04:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I found this.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:59.60,01:05:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go in there. I'll check it out.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:01.48,01:05:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- Give me a gun and a flashlight. \N- Don't be so John Wayne, you could get killed.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:07.57,01:05:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I've said that, \NI'm not going in there alone, either.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:10.91,01:05:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- I must go. \N- Let's all look.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:13.87,01:05:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just stay out here with Amy.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:15.62,01:05:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Not alone you won't. Kahega!
Dialogue: 0,01:05:43.81,01:05:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay close together. Homolka...
Dialogue: 0,01:05:53.03,01:05:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- Homolka! \N- The same hieroglyphics, over and over.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:59.66,01:06:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- What do they mean? \N- Homolka!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:08.63,01:06:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, don't wander off!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:11.09,01:06:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- So do you speak English? \N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:14.68,01:06:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's your name? \N- Claude.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:17.06,01:06:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Claude? Heh. That's an unusual name for \Nsomebody from, um... Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,01:06:23.56,01:06:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- Mombasa. \N- It's an unusual name for Mombasa.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:30.40,01:06:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- Have you ever been to Mombasa? \N- Uh, no.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:35.78,01:06:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what do you know about it?
Dialogue: 0,01:06:43.54,01:06:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go home.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:50.21,01:06:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy?
Dialogue: 0,01:06:54.01,01:06:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, come here.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:56.26,01:07:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you, girl? \NCome on, I'm not fooling around.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:03.56,01:07:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:05.90,01:07:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy?
Dialogue: 0,01:07:10.07,01:07:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here, girl. Amy.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:25.87,01:07:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles!
Dialogue: 0,01:07:29.88,01:07:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Charlie!
Dialogue: 0,01:07:33.59,01:07:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are those holes? \N- Lava tubes.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:35.97,01:07:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Molten rock must be flowing \Nthrough this whole place.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:39.01,01:07:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This must lead to the mine.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:42.97,01:07:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, bring a light.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:48.65,01:07:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:52.69,01:07:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:56.36,01:07:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Up here. No...!
Dialogue: 0,01:07:59.87,01:08:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's not going anywhere. \N- Where could they be? What happened?
Dialogue: 0,01:08:05.75,01:08:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit! Let's get out of \Nhere while we still can.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:09.13,01:08:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,01:08:11.04,01:08:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's that? \N- Richard!
Dialogue: 0,01:08:14.01,01:08:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- Richard? \N- Help me!
Dialogue: 0,01:08:19.34,01:08:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Richard! \N-
Dialogue: 0,01:08:20.26,01:08:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Richard! Oh, my God! Something...
Dialogue: 0,01:08:55.88,01:08:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- Richard. \N- Come on.
Dialogue: 0,01:08:57.51,01:08:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:03.26,01:09:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's okay. \N- Peter.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:20.86,01:09:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They're gorillas. \NThey're some kind of gorillas.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:26.04,01:09:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I never saw an animal move like \Nthat. They just... Look. They just kill.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:30.96,01:09:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the diamonds were never \Nfound. The myth of the killer ape is true.
Dialogue: 0,01:09:35.96,01:09:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:04.16,01:10:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Bad gorillas.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:10:07.41,01:10:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me turn your volume down.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:14.29,01:10:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's your lovey.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:19.30,01:10:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:21.22,01:10:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- It's</i> okay. \N<i>- Mother. Mother.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:10:25.68,01:10:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you're okay now.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:36.15,01:10:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- See anything? \N- No, but I'm the last line of defense.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:40.15,01:10:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They have sensor-operated machine pistols \Non tripods.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:42.07,01:10:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything comes within 40 ft., \Nget ready to the 4th of July.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:45.91,01:10:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What can I say, you \Nreally know how to pack.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:59.13,01:11:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't see anything. \N- Put that out.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:22.15,01:11:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They're testing their perimeter.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:32.33,01:11:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How intelligent are they?
Dialogue: 0,01:11:33.91,01:11:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Gorillas are very smart, \Nbut they're not aggressive.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:36.46,01:11:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- These things are very aggressive. \N- I'd say they're smart. Too damn smart.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:40.17,01:11:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They're out there, but what are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,01:11:43.80,01:11:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Monroe!
Dialogue: 0,01:12:43.78,01:12:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Get down!
Dialogue: 0,01:12:55.79,01:12:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- They're gone. \N- Couple of hours until first light.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:58.92,01:13:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we're out of here.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:03.38,01:13:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Those hieroglyphics \Nwe saw inscribed everywhere?
Dialogue: 0,01:13:09.26,01:13:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- I have translated them. \N- What do they say?
Dialogue: 0,01:13:11.64,01:13:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"We are watching you."
Dialogue: 0,01:13:29.28,01:13:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We must have hit some of them. \NWhere are the bodies?
Dialogue: 0,01:13:32.57,01:13:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- Have you seen Amy? She's gone. \N- No.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:34.70,01:13:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,She's joined the club, then. We've got two \Nporters missing and Homolka's run off, too.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:39.54,01:13:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm going to find her. \N- People come first, then gorillas.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:43.54,01:13:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- Do you agree? \N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:45.04,01:13:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. We'll retrieve our comrades, \Nthen we'll retrieve your missing gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:50.17,01:13:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll get the hell out of here. \NMount up!
Dialogue: 0,01:15:28.61,01:15:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the story. \NThey domesticated gorillas.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:31.90,01:15:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You call that \Ndomesticated? They're killing a man.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:34.82,01:15:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They taught them to be this way. \NThey bred them to violence.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:39.49,01:15:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They looked for the trait \Nand they encouraged it.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:43.25,01:15:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Guard dogs, and they \Nturned on their masters.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:48.46,01:15:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that smell?
Dialogue: 0,01:15:52.51,01:15:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all the bones of gorillas.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:54.47,01:15:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- You mean, these are...? \N- No, these are normal gorillas.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:00.22,01:16:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- This one's skull was crushed. \N- Feel that?
Dialogue: 0,01:16:03.06,01:16:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Feel what?
Dialogue: 0,01:16:20.28,01:16:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,01:16:29.67,01:16:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Everybody okay? \N- Yeah, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:35.97,01:16:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go this way. It's all caved in. \NGod, I'm so glad to see you.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:39.97,01:16:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- I was trying to find the mines... \N- Be quiet. Got any flares, Kahega?
Dialogue: 0,01:16:44.22,01:16:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,01:16:48.31,01:16:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's making my eyes burn? \N- Sulfur fumes.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:51.19,01:16:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hope there's another way out of here.
Dialogue: 0,01:17:06.87,01:17:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful.
Dialogue: 0,01:17:28.52,01:17:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- What the hell...? \N- It's the mines!
Dialogue: 0,01:17:33.27,01:17:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"We are watching you." It's the trainers \Ntalking. The teacher is watching you.
Dialogue: 0,01:17:38.61,01:17:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Dead teachers.
Dialogue: 0,01:17:45.53,01:17:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,01:17:51.87,01:17:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, yes. I knew it was true!
Dialogue: 0,01:17:58.01,01:18:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The city of Zinj, the diamonds...
Dialogue: 0,01:18:05.43,01:18:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Every word of it was absolutely true.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:12.77,01:18:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd leave those alone.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:20.95,01:18:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- Any other way out of here? \N- Not that I've noticed.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:25.57,01:18:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me. Fill up everything.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:39.13,01:18:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- You've got to get me out of here! \N- Take a number.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:42.30,01:18:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- But we're going to be rich! \N- ls that a way out?
Dialogue: 0,01:18:45.59,01:18:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:21.71,01:19:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,01:19:45.07,01:19:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- Let's go. \N- Stay close together.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:54.08,01:19:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- What is it? \N- It's a geode. A giant diamond.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:59.88,01:20:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- They cut him off. Kahega! \N- Check if there's a way out back there.
Dialogue: 0,01:20:13.18,01:20:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Kahega!
Dialogue: 0,01:20:39.50,01:20:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeffrey...
Dialogue: 0,01:20:43.05,01:20:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Charlie!
Dialogue: 0,01:20:45.88,01:20:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Charlie!
Dialogue: 0,01:20:48.63,01:20:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's him? \N- It's him.
Dialogue: 0,01:20:55.64,01:20:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:10.99,01:21:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- Is there a way out back there? \N- No, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:14.83,01:21:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- We're almost out of rounds. \N- Buy me two minutes.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:46.57,01:21:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me try.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:49.36,01:21:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Aah!
Dialogue: 0,01:22:22.27,01:22:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugly gorillas. Ugly. Go</i> away.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:28.78,01:22:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't know what to make of it.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:41.54,01:22:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- Amy. \N- Mother. Mother.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:22:50.05,01:22:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Peter hug <i>Amy.</i> \N- Maternal instinct, long may she reign.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:54.22,01:22:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are you doing? \N- What am I doing? I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:57.01,01:22:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,- We're getting out. \N- What about them?
Dialogue: 0,01:22:59.10,01:23:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Put them on \Nthe endangered species list.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:09.15,01:23:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Monroe. Let's go! Move!
Dialogue: 0,01:23:13.20,01:23:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- What the hell is that? \N- The latest thing in communication.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:16.45,01:23:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- Climb! \N- Up here.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:20.37,01:23:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- Go! Go! \N- Come on.
Dialogue: 0,01:24:01.16,01:24:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,01:24:09.42,01:24:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, girl. Come on!
Dialogue: 0,01:24:22.68,01:24:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,GO, Amy!
Dialogue: 0,01:24:46.33,01:24:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep going!
Dialogue: 0,01:24:50.58,01:24:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- Unh. \N- Come on, come on.
Dialogue: 0,01:24:57.09,01:24:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,01:25:01.14,01:25:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where are they? \N- I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:22.16,01:25:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,01:25:27.45,01:25:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,01:25:31.08,01:25:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- Go, Amy! \N- Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,01:25:34.04,01:25:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Just hurry! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,01:25:44.89,01:25:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come on! \N- You can do it!
Dialogue: 0,01:25:49.56,01:25:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep moving.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:51.85,01:25:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Head for higher ground.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:54.48,01:25:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep going, Amy!
Dialogue: 0,01:26:26.93,01:26:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Should be a big yellow case \Nwith a red stripe on that plane.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:30.18,01:26:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a balloon. I'll get the transmitter.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:35.06,01:26:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,01:26:40.94,01:26:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,01:26:43.70,01:26:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- How close is the border? \N- Not far.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:46.03,01:26:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Karen Ross, 81452.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:48.12,01:26:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That is KR 81452. \NHouston, Travis, do you read?
Dialogue: 0,01:26:53.50,01:26:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>KR 81452.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:26:56.75,01:26:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Houston, Travis, do you read?
Dialogue: 0,01:26:59.50,01:27:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,81452, that is KR 81452. \NHouston, Travis, do you read?
Dialogue: 0,01:27:08.64,01:27:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- Karen, is that you? \N<i>- It's</i> me, Travis.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:12.68,01:27:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd lost you. \NI sent another expedition.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:15.81,01:27:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- Did</i> you get <i>it?</i> \N- I have bad news. Charles was killed.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:22.36,01:27:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get the diamond? Did you?
Dialogue: 0,01:27:30.33,01:27:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- Yes.</i> \N- Good girl.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:36.67,01:27:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember when I told you \Nthat if I ever knew you sent me here...
Dialogue: 0,01:27:42.51,01:27:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for some diamond, \Nand not for Charlie, I'd make you sorry?
Dialogue: 0,01:27:47.76,01:27:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>Karen, of course I'm upset.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:27:50.81,01:27:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>- But what's done is done. I could...</i> \N- I <i>know. You need</i> a <i>new</i> cash <i>machine.</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:27:56.10,01:27:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>What would happen to the satellite...</i>
Dialogue: 0,01:27:57.98,01:28:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,if I put its phone number in the laser \Nand pulled the trigger?
Dialogue: 0,01:28:01.15,01:28:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The chip from the transmitter's \Ngot the satellite's number.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:08.37,01:28:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a 12,000 channel chip. \NIf you put it through the diamond... Karen!
Dialogue: 0,01:28:19.33,01:28:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is for you, Charlie.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:25.01,01:28:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,01:28:29.72,01:28:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,01:28:34.02,01:28:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There you are.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:44.53,01:28:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, you saved me.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:49.36,01:28:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,01:29:08.72,01:29:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,01:29:14.35,01:29:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you, too.
Dialogue: 0,01:29:18.35,01:29:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother?
Dialogue: 0,01:29:23.36,01:29:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see. It's Africa. It's your mother.
Dialogue: 0,01:29:28.03,01:29:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,01:29:32.99,01:29:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Good gorillas? What good gorillas?
Dialogue: 0,01:29:44.96,01:29:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Handsome fella.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:12.07,01:30:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy...
Dialogue: 0,01:30:20.16,01:30:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that. \Nls that Amy with the...?
Dialogue: 0,01:30:22.87,01:30:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The silverback. So she's...
Dialogue: 0,01:30:28.55,01:30:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. I see.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:35.80,01:30:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She's home.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:54.99,01:30:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- Will she be all right? \N- They know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:57.53,01:30:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's us I'm worried about.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:58.99,01:31:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- We've got to go. Come on. \N- Bye, Amy.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:37.70,01:31:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- Peter, would you do me a favor? \N- What?
Dialogue: 0,01:31:40.45,01:31:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you throw this away for me.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:43.16,01:31:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure?
Dialogue: 0,01:31:48.04,01:31:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:55.68,01:31:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- There's a wind. \N- I hope it blows us someplace good.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:59.60,01:32:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
